# Reverse proxy for api.yourpersonas.com — Caddy provisions and renews the
# TLS certificate automatically (ACME/Let's Encrypt) as long as DNS for this
# domain points at the VM and ports 80/443 are reachable from the internet.
# No other config needed: this IS the whole production TLS setup.
#
# TRUSTED_PROXIES in .env must include this container's address on the
# compose network (see docker-compose.prod.yml) so the Go app's
# ParseTrustedProxies (TICKET-26) trusts the X-Forwarded-For header Caddy
# sets below — otherwise c.RealIP() sees Caddy's IP for every request,
# breaking per-IP rate limiting (TICKET-22) and Turnstile's remoteip
# (TICKET-11). See docs/deploy_runbook.md for the exact value.
api.yourpersonas.com {
	reverse_proxy api:8080
}
